Privacy Policy
Last Revised: April 25, 2024
Social Social Apps is providing this Privacy Policy to inform users of our policies and procedures regarding the collection, use, and disclosure of personal information received from users of (i) this website, (ii) any other website that is owned and operated by Social Social Apps or its affiliates, (iii) any Social Social Apps-owned or affiliated mobile device application (the "App(s)"). The Websites and Apps are collectively referred to as the "services." In this Privacy Policy, "you" or "your" refers to the person using the services and the company (if any) on whose behalf you are acting, and "we," "us," "our," "Social Social Apps," or the "Company" refers to Social Social Apps and its affiliates. We may update this privacy policy periodically for any reason, and each version will apply to information collected while it is in effect. You will be notified of any material changes to our privacy policy by posting the new privacy policy on our website. Please check this privacy policy periodically for any changes. Before using the services or submitting any personal information to Social Social Apps, please read this Privacy Policy carefully and contact us at
sociasocialapps@gmail.com
if you have any questions. By using the Services, you accept our Privacy Policy, which is incorporated by reference into our Terms of Use. Please do not access the sites or otherwise use the services if you do not agree with this privacy policy.
Insofar as we obtain the consent of the data subject for processing operations involving personal data, Art. 6 (1) (a) of the EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) serves as the legal basis for the processing of personal data. When processing personal data that is necessary for the performance of a contract to which the data subject is a party, Art. 6 (1) (b) DSGVO serves as the legal basis. This also applies to processing operations that are necessary for the performance of pre-contractual measures. Insofar as processing of personal data is necessary for compliance with a legal obligation to which our company is subject, Art. 6 (1) lit. c DSGVO serves as the legal basis. In the event that vital interests of the data subject or another natural person make processing of personal data necessary, Art. 6 (1) lit. d DSGVO serves as the legal basis. If the processing is necessary to protect a legitimate interest of our company or a third party and the interests, fundamental rights and freedoms of the data subject do not override the first-mentioned interest, Art. 6 (1) f DSGVO serves as the legal basis for the processing.
