We collect personally identifiable information to provide our services to you, to communicate with you, and to administer your registered user account, should you have one.
Information we collect:
Through the Site, we may collect the following categories of personal information about you, including, but not limited to:
Registration Information: In order to use certain features of the services, you must register and create an account. When creating an account, you will be asked for basic registration information such as your email address, username, and password.
Identification Information: We may also ask you to provide identification information to confirm your identity, including your first and last name, username, address, and telephone number.
Commercial Information: We may keep a history of the content you browse, the services you use, or the stocks and people you follow through the services.
Third Party Services Information: To display information to you through the Services, we may collect, on your behalf, your account and other personal information from third party services that you register under your account through the Services.
Technical and navigational information: We collect information about your interaction with our website, including the browser you use, pages visited, average time spent on our Website, IP address, unique device identifier for mobile devices, operating system version, and app version.
Location Information: If you elect to use location-based services, we may collect location information from your device. You can control or disable the sharing of location information through your device settings and/or your browser settings.
Social Media Information: We operate pages on social media sites such as Instagram, Facebook, Twitter, YouTube, and LinkedIn ("Social Media Sites"). When you engage with our Social Media Pages, we collect personally identifiable information that you voluntarily provide to us, such as your contact information. Additionally, the companies that host our social media pages may provide us with aggregate information and analytics about the use of our social media pages.
Information about Email Opening/Clicking: We might include pixels in our email marketing campaigns that enable us to capture your email and IP address, along with the date and time you open an email or click on a hyperlink in the e-mail.
Other Information: We might ask for or collect other personal information, like feedback, questions, comments, suggestions, or other ideas, in to provide you with additional benefits or to enhance the services. In such instances, you may be given the option to provide or refuse to provide such information.
If you activate the mobile device options, if available, we will capture your mobile phone number. If you contact us via email through the Website, we may keep a record of your contact information and communications and we may use your email address and any other information you provided in your message to reply to you.
Use of Contact Information:
Additionally, we might make use of your contact information to market to you and provide you with information regarding our products and services, including, but not restricted to, our services. If at any time you determine that you no longer want to receive such information from us, please follow the opt-out instructions included in each of the communications. We might aggregate Personal Information and then use the aggregated data to evaluate the overall effectiveness of our services, to enhance our services and introduce new features, and for other related purposes. Additionally, we might occasionally analyze the overall behavior and characteristics of the users of our services and may share aggregate information, such as overall user stats, with potential business affiliates. We may gather aggregate information via the services, through cookies, and through other means outlined in this Privacy Policy. We also may use your contact information for the following purposes:
To provide you with administrative updates, such as information about the services and modifications to our terms, conditions, and policies;
To understand how you engage with our services;
To sustain and to enhance the services;
Development of new services and products;
To protect against fraud, criminal activities or abuse of our services and to maintain the security of our IT systems, architecture and networks; and
To meet legal requirements and to comply with legal proceedings, and to ensure our rights, privacy, security, or property and/or those of our affiliates, you, or other third parties are protected.
All of these purposes also represent our legitimate interests, which we pursue with the processing of personal data associated with each of them. The legal basis is accordingly Art. 6 para. 1 p. 1 lit. f) DSGVO).
Log Dat:
When you access our site, our servers will automatically capture information that web browsers transmit when you view a web page ("Log Data"). This Log Data can include information like your IP address, browser type, the way you came to our site, the web pages you viewed, the search terms you used, any advertisements you clicked on. We utilize the log data to monitor the use of the services and for the purposes of technical administration of the services. We do not link your IP address to other personally identifiable data to identify you personally except when we must do so to enforce our Terms of Use. The legal basis for the temporary storage of the data and the log files is Art. 6 para. 1 lit. f DSGVO.
As many other websites, we use " cookie " technology to gather additional information regarding the usage of the site to optimize the services. A cookie is a little data file which we transfer to the hard drive of your computer. We are not using cookies to collect any personally identifiable information. We may store cookies on your computer for various time periods. Social Social Apps can use both session cookies and permanent cookies to understand how you engage with the services better, to track overall utilization by our users and routing of browser traffic on the services, to deliver promotions on the services that are customized to meet your preferences, and to improve the services. A session cookie allows certain functionalities of the website and our services and will be cleared from your computer when you disconnect from or exit the website. A permanent cookie remains after you close your browser and can be used by your browser on subsequent visits to the website. Permanent cookies can be removed by following the guidance in your web browser's help file. Most web browsers will automatically accept cookies. More details about cookies can be found in All about cookies.
You will be able to adjust your browser preferences to disable the cookie acceptance or to request you to accept a cookie from the websites you visit.
Please be aware that if you restrict website cookies, you might not be able to access parts of the services and the services may not work as they should.
Advertising platforms might use cookies to gather personal information. Many advertising networks offer you the ability to opt-out of targeted advertising. If you want to know more about this, please visit the Network Advertising Initiative's online resources and read the opt-out information there. If you visit the website from your mobile device, you might not have the ability to control tracking technologies from the settings
Type of Cookies Used:
The website makes use of the following technologies outlined hereafter.
Strictly Necessary Cookies. We use cookies which are strictly necessary to enable users to be able to enter the website and use certain features of it, such as being able to log in and gain access to safe areas. These cookies are crucial for the use and navigation of the website. Without those cookies, fundamental features of our website would not function. As these cookies are necessary for the operation of the website, users are not able to opt out of them.
Optional cookies. We use "analytics" cookies that enable us to track and count the amount of users who have visited the website, and to understand how visitors navigate around the site when they use it. This helps us enhance the functionality of our website, for instance, by assuring that visitors can easily find exactly what they need. Those cookies only give us anonymous traffic metrics (like the number of page visits), the amount of visitors, and the amount of the time spent on every page. These cookies also enable us to monitor how frequently people click on posts on third-party websites, for example, on social media. In the framework of using Google Analytics, optional cookies from Google are placed on our website. Google Analytics is a web analytics service offered by Google, Inc. ("Google"). Google Analytics utilizes cookies to understand how users are interacting with the Services. The cookie generated information regarding your use of the website (including your IP address) will be transferred to Google and saved by Google on their servers. This information will be used by Google to analyze your use of the services, to compile reports on website activity for us and to provide other services related to the use of the website and the Internet. Google might also transmit this information to third parties if it is legally mandated to do so or if third parties are processing this information on behalf of Google. If you want to know more about how Google Analytics gathers and makes use of personal data, please read the privacy policy, which can be accessed here: Google Privacy Policy. To deactivate detection by Google Analytics on all websites, visit http://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout. By making use of the services, you agree to the data gathered about you being handled by Google in the previously mentioned manner and for the above-mentioned purpose. The website uses other analytics cookies which are provided by third parties and are similar to Google Analytics cookies, and also include links from the website to plug-ins (e.g. social media services) and websites or applications run by third parties. We do not have control over third party services and are not accountable for the collected information from them.
