Personal Information:
Unless otherwise specified in this Privacy Policy, we do not sell, disclose, or provide your personal information to any third party for their marketing purposes without your permission. In association with third-party services, we might disclose some of your personal information to those third-party service providers to fulfill the transaction you have requested. We might disclose your personal information to third-party service providers so that they can support us in completing your requests or transactions that you perform through the sites, including the operation of specific site functions and services. Third parties who act on our behalf and obtain access to your personal data are required by contract to comply with our data protection principles and are not allowed to use the information for any other means. We reserve the right, in our sole discretion, to disclose or share your personal information with law enforcement agencies, government officials, and other third parties:
To reply to subpoenas, court orders, or legal processes;
To investigate, prevent, or take any other action concerning breaches of our Terms of Use, illegal activities, suspected fraud, or any situation that may pose a potential risk to the rights or physical safety of any person, or to the safety of our network, sites, or services;
Respond to allegations that a post or other content violates the third party rights;
In an emergency, to be able to protect the health and security of users of our websites or the public; or
To the extent necessary under applicable law.
We might disclose your personal information to other third-parties with your permission or at your instructions.
