While Social Social Apps will not disclose personally identifiable information to third-party advertisers, if an advertiser asks Social Social Apps to show an advertisement to users with particular characteristics or a certain segment of that group (e.g., males aged 25-30 who have viewed specific content categories on the services), and you are responsive to that advertisement, the third-party advertiser might consider that you have the characteristics of the target audience it is seeking to address.
