We will keep your personal information for as long as necessary for the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy, for so long as we have a valid business reason for doing so, or as long as it is required by law, whichever is longer. Unless we are otherwise obligated to maintain compliance with any industry regulation or law, we will only keep your personal information for a minimum of two years after the withdrawal of an authorization request.
In establishing the reasonable storage period for your personal information, we will also consider the amount, nature and sensitivity of the personal information, the potential risk of harm from any unauthorized use or exposure of your personal information, the purposes for which we use your personal information as well as if we can achieve those purposes by other means, and applicable legal restrictions.
